<body>
    <h1>Privacy Discussions</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <ul>
<style>[data-colorid=3Dh2vzp6ld49]{color:#36b37e} html[data-color-mode=3Dda=
rk] [data-colorid=3Dh2vzp6ld49]{color:#4cc994}[data-colorid=3Dth6j18es3b]{c=
olor:#36b37e} html[data-color-mode=3Ddark] [data-colorid=3Dth6j18es3b]{colo=
r:#4cc994}[data-colorid=3Dnwcuj32vpx]{color:#36b37e} html[data-color-mode=
=3Ddark] [data-colorid=3Dnwcuj32vpx]{color:#4cc994}[data-colorid=3Dx96hs8x7=
y1]{color:#36b37e} html[data-color-mode=3Ddark] [data-colorid=3Dx96hs8x7y1]=
{color:#4cc994}[data-colorid=3Dkdoib5h5pq]{color:#36b37e} html[data-color-m=
ode=3Ddark] [data-colorid=3Dkdoib5h5pq]{color:#4cc994}[data-colorid=3Dx14mt=
rpixn]{color:#36b37e} html[data-color-mode=3Ddark] [data-colorid=3Dx14mtrpi=
xn]{color:#4cc994}</style>
<li>
<p>We would need a way for a customer to get/revoke consent even if they pr=
eviously gave it.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Potential Privacy Notice updates</p></li>
<li>
<p>I=E2=80=99m curious to know if they still see value in this idea if we w=
ere to have an agreement with Uber/Lyft.&nbsp; I think they would because o=
f the DOOH use case they mention, but they should sync with BD because I be=
lieve we=E2=80=99re in discussions with Uber on this topic.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><span data-colorid=3D"kdoib5h5pq">Rideshare was my proof-of-concept, sin=
ce we already have the hardware with Bluetooth capabilities, and Octopus ha=
s gone down the rabbit hole of implementing something like this previously,=
 just without the CarrierID component. If there's sufficient interest, then=
 expanding to the Retail Media Network at large&nbsp;</span><em><span data-=
colorid=3D"x14mtrpixn">shouldn't</span></em><span data-colorid=3D"nwcuj32vp=
x">&nbsp;pose a large issue, so we'd expand to other DOOH use cases</span><=
/p></li>
<li>
<p><span data-colorid=3D"x96hs8x7y1">Not sure on the particulars for the Ri=
deshare/Uber negotiations, but using Bluetooth like this would allow us to =
get a carrier ID, which I believe is planned to be a large part of business=
 with MAIDs going away. Uber can tell us a fair bit about the user, but unl=
ess they'd be providing us with the device's IP, we wouldn't be able to get=
 a Carrier ID directly. There's more discussion here, and with CID so nebul=
ous still I don't want to fall into idle speculation</span></p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Have they synced with the Adapt team?&nbsp; One of the issues we are wor=
king on with the Adapt team is that Adapt does not (currently) have a custo=
mer consent flow.&nbsp; If we went forward with this project, it would prob=
ably have to be integrated into the Adapt consent.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Not necessarily a privacy question, but I=E2=80=99m curious about how mu=
ch power this uses.&nbsp; I know it says it=E2=80=99s a =E2=80=9Clow power=
=E2=80=9D Bluetooth signal, but customers might not love learning that thei=
r phone is sending out a constant signal in the off chance that they might =
possibly take a rideshare and be targeted with ads.&nbsp; I think this woul=
d also affect any opt-in rate depending on how we ultimately word the notic=
e and consent.</p></li>
<li>
<p>They say this is based on the covid exposure tech that Google and Apple =
deployed during the pandemic.&nbsp; I just looked at the exposure notificat=
ion materials on my iPhone and there=E2=80=99s a lot there =E2=80=93 opt-in=
, extensive explanations with details on how the tech works and what it=E2=
=80=99s used for, etc.&nbsp; I don=E2=80=99t know if we would necessarily h=
ave to replicate that, but I do think they=E2=80=99ll need to benchmark aga=
inst that.&nbsp; It would also be interesting to know how many people opted=
-in to the covid exposure programs.&nbsp; I=E2=80=99m not sure if that=E2=
=80=99s publicly available, but it would provide some sort of number to pro=
ject against.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Is the purpose just to tell an advertiser that somebody saw their ad (i.=
e. analytics/reporting) or is the purpose to provide the rider personalized=
 ads?</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><span data-colorid=3D"th6j18es3b">Targeting - We have some data about th=
e rider, we can serve them more relevant ads</span></p></li>
<li>
<p><span data-colorid=3D"h2vzp6ld49">Measurement - We know who was sitting =
in the ridershare vehicle and can know that they saw a specific ad.</span><=
/p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>If it=E2=80=99s for analytics/reporting, why isn=E2=80=99t the sensor in=
 the tablet sufficient (the one that provides a silhouette to indicate a pa=
ssenger is in the seat)?</p></li>
<li>
<p>It seems from this that they want to be able to track that user through =
the advertising lifecycle (seeing the add =C3=A0 sale), which is why the ta=
blet sensor isn=E2=80=99t sufficient; how would that happen?&nbsp; In other=
 words, how would we combine the rider with a conversion?</p></li>
<li>
<p>What would the report back to the advertiser look like?&nbsp; Is it aggr=
egated/anonymized?</p></li>
</ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
